sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    participant User as User / Client
    participant LSD as Llama Stack Server<br/>8321/TCP HTTP
    participant Inline as GarakInlineEvalAdapter
    participant Remote as GarakRemoteEvalAdapter
    participant Garak as garak subprocess
    participant KFP as KFP API (DSPA)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant KFPPod as KFP Pipeline Pod
    participant LLM as Target LLM (vLLM)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Shield as Shield Models<br/>(Llama Guard)
    participant S3 as S3 Object Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant FilesAPI as Llama Stack Files API
    participant EvalHub as Eval-Hub Service
    participant Adapter as GarakAdapter<br/>(Eval-Hub)
    participant Sidecar as Eval-Hub Sidecar
    participant OCI as OCI Registry<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant MLflow as MLflow<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    rect rgb(232, 245, 233)
        Note over User,FilesAPI: Flow 1: Inline Garak Scan (Llama Stack)
        User->>LSD: POST /eval/run_eval<br/>Auth: None
        LSD->>Inline: dispatch to inline provider
        Inline->>Inline: deep-merge benchmark config
        Inline->>Garak: spawn subprocess (os.setsid)<br/>timeout + SIGTERM/SIGKILL
        Garak->>LLM: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer Token<br/>TLS: Configurable
        LLM-->>Garak: Model response
        Garak-->>Inline: Scan results + reports
        Inline->>FilesAPI: Upload results (in-process)
        Inline-->>LSD: Job ID + status
        LSD-->>User: Scan results
    end

    rect rgb(227, 242, 253)
        Note over User,S3: Flow 2: Remote KFP Garak Scan (Llama Stack)
        User->>LSD: POST /eval/run_eval<br/>Auth: None
        LSD->>Remote: dispatch to remote provider
        Remote->>KFP: Submit pipeline run<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (SA)<br/>TLS: HTTPS
        KFP->>KFPPod: Create pipeline step pod
        KFPPod->>LLM: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer Token<br/>TLS: Configurable
        LLM-->>KFPPod: Model response
        KFPPod->>S3: Upload artifacts<br/>Auth: AWS IAM
        KFPPod->>FilesAPI: Upload results<br/>HTTP 8321/TCP
        Remote-->>LSD: Job ID (KFP run ID)
        User->>LSD: GET /eval/jobs/status
        LSD->>Remote: poll status
        Remote->>KFP: GET run status<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (SA)
        KFP-->>Remote: Run status
        Remote-->>LSD: Status response
        LSD-->>User: Job status + results
    end

    rect rgb(252, 228, 236)
        Note over EvalHub,MLflow: Flow 3: Eval-Hub Simple Mode
        EvalHub->>Adapter: K8s Job (ConfigMap mount)<br/>/meta/job.json
        Adapter->>Adapter: Parse JobSpec<br/>mode: simple
        Adapter->>Sidecar: POST status: RUNNING
        Adapter->>Garak: spawn subprocess
        Garak->>LLM: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
        LLM-->>Garak: Model response
        Garak-->>Adapter: Scan results
        Adapter->>OCI: Push artifact bundle<br/>Auth: Registry creds<br/>TLS: HTTPS
        Adapter->>MLflow: Log metrics + artifacts<br/>TLS: Configurable
        Adapter->>Sidecar: POST status: COMPLETED<br/>+ metrics + results
    end

    rect rgb(255, 243, 224)
        Note over EvalHub,MLflow: Flow 4: Eval-Hub KFP Mode
        EvalHub->>Adapter: K8s Job (ConfigMap mount)
        Adapter->>Adapter: Parse JobSpec<br/>mode: kfp
        Adapter->>Sidecar: POST status: RUNNING
        Adapter->>KFP: Submit pipeline<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (SA)
        KFP->>KFPPod: Create step pods
        KFPPod->>LLM: Probe prompts<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
        LLM-->>KFPPod: Responses
        KFPPod->>S3: Upload scan artifacts<br/>Auth: AWS IAM
        Adapter->>KFP: Poll run status
        KFP-->>Adapter: Run complete
        Adapter->>S3: Download results<br/>Auth: AWS IAM
        Adapter->>OCI: Push artifact bundle<br/>Auth: Registry creds
        Adapter->>MLflow: Log metrics + artifacts
        Adapter->>Sidecar: POST status: COMPLETED
    end

    rect rgb(243, 229, 245)
        Note over KFPPod,S3: Flow 5: Intents Benchmark Pipeline (KFP)
        Note right of KFPPod: 6-step pipeline
        KFPPod->>KFPPod: Step 1: validate (garak import check)
        KFPPod->>S3: Step 2: resolve_taxonomy<br/>(fetch custom or use built-in)
        KFPPod->>LLM: Step 3: sdg_generate<br/>Auth: SDG_API_KEY
        LLM-->>KFPPod: Synthetic prompts
        KFPPod->>S3: Step 4: prepare_prompts<br/>Upload CSVs
        KFPPod->>LLM: Step 5a: garak_scan<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
        KFPPod->>LLM: Step 5b: TAP attack<br/>Auth: ATTACKER_API_KEY
        KFPPod->>LLM: Step 5c: Judge classify<br/>Auth: JUDGE_API_KEY
        KFPPod->>S3: Step 6: write_kfp_outputs<br/>Download + format results
    end
